The Tragedy of Numerical Ambition.

Romeo, a well-versed man in the art of number.
Juliet, a maiden fair, muse to the arithmetic gods.

                    Act I: The Entanglement of Two Souls.

                    Scene I: The Whisper of Intents.

[Enter Romeo and Juliet]

Romeo:
 Listen to your heart; let thine inner value be known.

Juliet:
 Pray, listen to thy heart; impart thy deepest numeral unto me.

[Exeunt]

                    Act II: The Discourse of Calculation.

                    Scene I: The Conjunction of Fates.

[Enter Romeo and Juliet]

Romeo:
 Thou art as spirited as the morning dew upon the meadow.

Juliet:
 Art thou as bountiful as the sum of the most beauteous rose and the brightest star in the firmament?

Romeo:
 If not, let us proceed to scene II.
 If so, let memory hold fast to the sum of the gentle rose and yon celestial body.

[Exit Romeo]
[Enter Romeo]

Juliet:
 Thou art as radiant as the morning sun; yea, as the sum of thy own self and the greatest of all kings!

[Exeunt]

                    Scene II: The Axiom of Our Tale.

[Enter Romeo and Juliet]

Romeo:
 My love, recall the soft whispers of our hearts; speak it forth!

Juliet:
 Am I as modest as the sum of the smallest stone and the meekest mouse?

Romeo:
 If not, to the next chapter of our story let us swiftly sail.
 If so, treasure my words as thou wouldst treasure thine own soul.

[Exeunt]

                    Act III: The Denouement.

                    Scene I: The Unveiling of Truth.

[Enter Juliet]

Juliet:
 O Fortune, recall the fondness I hold for thee; let it be heard!

[Exeunt]
